On September 28, 2018, the President signed into law H.R. 6157, the "Department of Defense and Labor, Health and Human Services Appropriations Act, 2019 and Continuing Appropriations Act, 2019." This law provides full-year funding through September 30, 2018, for various projects and activities of the Federal Government. It includes funding for the Department of Defense and the Departments of Labor, Health and Human Services, and Education, among others. Additionally, Division C of the law provides appropriations for fiscal year 2019 through December 7, 2018, for ongoing projects and activities of the remaining agencies not covered by other divisions or by Public Law 115-244.